The pre-fight screen may have been difficult to switch chr banks fast enough and get that synced up without using MMC2. During the fight, I'm not really sure what good reason there was if any to not just use a sprite hit zero. I'm sure the game could have been made without it. But they had it and designed it to use it. Really I think Nintendo was just experimenting. I don't think they really thought out how useful or not the MMC2 CHR switching would be.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Wed Feb 22, 2012 7:07 am</p><hr />
